Brief description:
This website allows users to enter a student name and five subject marks, calculate total and average, 
determine a grade and pass/fail status, and save multiple results into a history list that can be updated dynamically.

Target users:
Students and lecturers who want a quick way to calculate results and keep a small record during practice.

JavaScript features used:

Variables to store values (name, total, average, etc.)

Arrays for subjects, marks, and saved history

Arithmetic operators (+, /) for total and average

Comparison operators (>=, <) for grading and validation

innerHTML to update the webpage dynamically

Button click events (Calculate, Save, Remove, Reset)

Array indexing to read/display marks

push() and pop() to manage saved history

Technologies used:
HTML, JavaScript, (Basic CSS)